\begin_layout Plain Layout

   The conditional variance, h(t), of a FIGARCH(1,d,1) process is modeled
 as follows:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

   h(t) = omega + [1-beta L - phi L  (1-L)^d] epsilon(t)^2 + beta * h(t-1)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

   where L is the lag operator which is estimated using an ARCH(oo) representati
on,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

   h(t) = omega + sum(lambda(i) * epsilon(t-1)^2)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

   where lambda(i) is a function of the fractional differencing parameter,
 phi and beta.
\end_layout

